    <p>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div><a href="http://www.acm.org/technews/articles/2005-7/0314m.html#item16">ACM News Service: Our Frankenputer</a>.&nbsp; This blurb looks at a variety of hardware fixes and software solutions for improving security of the PC.&nbsp; The idea is to have PCs designed with security in mind.&nbsp; While I think that is a good idea, I would like to look more at where Peter Neumann points concerning the user culture and our part in the insecurity of our systems, at least among developers-as-users and power users who do not take appropriate and already-available precautions.<br /><br />The Philip E. Ross, 2005-03-14 <a href="http://www.forbes.com/business/global/2005/0314/042.html"><em>Forbes.com </em>article</a> has the following provocative lead:&nbsp; "Hostile programs bend our computers to their own purposes because we designed them that way. Time for some new ideas."&nbsp; Now just exactly who is this <em>we</em> they're talking about?<div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
